Being a wife of a farmer isn't easy. Isn't hard either, just... specific. 15 years ago I gave up my city life for the sake of our love and I am still not sure if it was worth it. We have a calm routine life, and if we lived alone in this town it would be fine, but the community feels odd sometimes. The seniors of our town (which have recently included my husband) have a weekly meeting at a slaughter house - odd, isn't it..? Some visitors only stay for 3-5 days or so and then disappear. It makes me very anxious. My husband says that they just leave by river. And he doesn't listen to me when I say thet every night before the visitors leave the pigs in a slaughter house seem to scream louder then usual. He is very calm, I suppose because he is much more sociable, he knows the people. But at least the sausages are soo delicious. They say that the recipe is a secret, but my neighbour said that they put pepper inside. Pretty excited to try it out!
